org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype

Class OntUnits

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype.OntUnits

  • public class OntUnits
extends Object
    This class is part of a data structure to provide the BCO ontology data (state values of sensors and actuators). The custom data type OntUnits expresses the top-level of the data structure (highest granularity), which includes a quantity of elements (1:N - relation). Consider in addition the data types OntProviderServices and OntStateChange. 1 : N 1 : N OntUnits --- (includes) --- OntProviderServices --- (includes) --- OntStateChange
    Author:
    agatting on 15.09.17.

      • addOntProviderService

        public void addOntProviderService(String unitId,
                                  String ontProviderService,
                                  OntStateChange ontStateChange)
                           throws org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException
        Method adds a new entry to the ontUnits hashMap. If there is an existing unitId entry, the ontProviderService with ontStateChange will be added to the related OntProviderServices value. Otherwise a new OntProviderServices will be created.
        Parameters:
        unitId - is the unitId extracted from the ontology.
        ontProviderService - is the providerService extracted from the ontology.
        ontStateChange - is the stateChange extracted from the ontology.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException - is thrown in case at least one parameter is null.
